At last, however, her listless walk brought her up alongside him, and still he said nothing. The cruelty of fooled honesty is often great after enlightenment, and it was mighty in Clare now. The outdoor air had apparently taken away from him all tendency to act on impulse; she knew that he saw her without irradiation – in all her bareness.

Time was chanting his satiric psalm at Tess then –

Behold, when thy face is made bare, he that loved thee shall hate;
